article.headline: Eastern Kentucky 85, SE Missouri State 81
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Matt Witt scored 25 points, including two key free throws with 10 seconds left, as Eastern Kentucky beat Southeast Missouri 85-81 Thursday night. Witt hit nine of 17 shots and had seven assists for the night. Ben Rushing added 23 points and Jon Bentley 16. Bentley added eight rebounds for the Colonels (12-12, 7-6 OVC). Southeast (10-14, 3-10) got 28 points from Derek Winans, who hit nine of 12 shots from the field, going 5-for-5 from 3-point range. Reggie Golson added 14 points, hitting seven of 11 shots. Daimon Gonner added 13 points and Norman Prather contributed 10 points. Southeast controlled most of the first half, jumping out to an 11-2 lead and leading by 15 (42-27) with 5:33 to go in the half. The first half was an offensive showcase, with Southeast shooting 65 percent from the field and Eastern shooting 61 percent. By halftime the Indians owned a 46-39 lead. The Colonels stormed back in the second half, taking their first lead with 17:38 to play. Southeast took its last lead, 77-76, when Winans hit a 3-pointer with less than three minutes remaining. Golson tied the game 79-79 with 1:20 left, but Bentley made a layup with 34 seconds to play, making it 81-79. The Indians turned the ball over with 11 seconds on the clock and were forced to foul. Witt and Rushing combined for four straight free throws to cement the win.
